    detail: "At the exclusive northernmost point of Koh Samui stands an elegant modern retreat, raised high above Tongson Bay with sweeping views over the island's northeast coast — a rare aspect that catches both Samui's famous sunrises and its sunsets. Open-plan volumes link indoor and outdoor living effortlessly, opening onto a breezy terrace, an infinity pool and a sun deck dressed with semi-submerged sunbeds, double daybeds and oversized umbrellas.\n\nThe signature gesture is a distinctive circular sunken seating sala set within a shallow pool at the terrace edge — the ideal spot for sunset drinks, games or quiet ocean-gazing — set beside a circular decorative helipad deck conceived for sunset events and photographs (ornamental, not an operational landing pad). Outdoor dining sits beneath a cantilevered canopy at a sixteen-seat table with its own service bar and lounge, while the open-plan living and dining room pairs sleek interiors with a 90-inch screen and a handcrafted table for ten.\n\nNine en-suite bedrooms across three floors — seven original suites plus two newer additions and a dedicated children's room — host up to twenty adults and a child. Exclusive amenities run deep: a private cinema, an adults' games lounge with open bar, a fully equipped gym, a sea-view sauna for four, an ice bath, an in-villa massage bed and an outdoor space for Muay Thai or yoga over the sea — all underpinned by full backup power and a resident manager, private chef and housekeeping, fifteen minutes from the airport and a short walk to Thong Sai Beach.",
