    blurb: "An extraordinary four-bedroom villa built into a lush rocky cliff in the exclusive Santikhiri Estate — its living spaces cascade down four storeys of timber decks and stone terraces to a waterfall plunge pool, with a 180-degree view across the Gulf of Siam.",
    detail: "Built into a lush hillside in the exclusive Santikhiri Estate, this extraordinary four-bedroom villa commands a breathtaking 180-degree panorama across the Gulf of Siam. The 900 m² property is designed to cascade down toward the ocean, its living spaces following the natural slope of the cliff: a series of timber decks and stone terraces descends over four storeys to a deck with a private plunge pool, a man-made waterfall and sunbeds, while a separate platform doubles as a yoga deck and sunset lounge — every room thoughtfully integrated with the landscape.\n\nThe interiors are seriously chic and entirely un-templated — no two spaces alike. Floor-to-ceiling glass doors invite the outdoors in, and vintage and designer furnishings sit alongside carefully curated artworks for a unique, welcoming atmosphere throughout. Guests share an open-plan living room with a projector for movie nights and a SONOS sound system, a minimalist kitchen, an outdoor bar, an outdoor wet kitchen and an al-fresco dining area for up to eight.\n\nFour stylish en-suite bedrooms each open to a private balcony, with two massage beds and a yoga deck for wellness, and a communal estate pool a short walk up the hill. Fully staffed with a villa manager, housekeeper and handyman, the stay includes a welcome drink and daily breakfast, with a private chef, in-villa spa and tailored tours available on request — a short drive from Lamai Beach and the Kamalaya wellness sanctuary.",
