    beds: 5, bedsLabel: "5", guests: 12, guestsLabel: "12", occupancy: "up to 12 guests", size: "2,000 m²",
    nightlyNum: 835, nightly: "from $835", note: "Fully staffed · breakfast included", sleeps: "12 guests · 5 bedrooms",
    blurb: "A five-bedroom hillside villa defined by a single soaring, wood-lined vaulted pavilion — its living level runs almost the full length of the house behind bi-folding glass on both sides, framing palm-clad valleys, Bophut bay and the offshore islands above a 20-metre infinity pool.",
    detail: "A slice of unmatched tropical elegance in the Bophut Hills, this five-bedroom villa centres on a vast, elevated living and dining pavilion that runs almost the entire length of the property beneath a soaring, wood-lined vaulted ceiling. Bi-folding glass doors on both sides open the room completely, ensuring constant panoramic views across palm-clad valleys and out to the bay of Bophut and the offshore islands, while a covered balcony with all-weather chairs runs the full length of the pavilion above the garden and pool.\n\nA pedestal table for ten anchors the dining area beside an open-plan kitchen with island breakfast bar, top-of-the-range appliances and a built-in wine cooler; the lounge is layered with deep upholstered sofas, a rustic coffee table, a Smart TV and a modern chandelier. Stairs on both sides lead down to three king guest bedrooms that look across the garden, pool and view, each with an en-suite rain-shower bathroom along a covered walkway, with a lawn extending to the wide pool terrace.\n\nThe 20-metre infinity pool has sunken stools at a swim-up bar set within a covered sala with dining bench seats. The villa's two mirror-image master suites — one opening directly onto the pool terrace, one above — each carry their own vaulted wooden ceiling, dressing area, twin washbasins, rain shower and a terrazzo bathtub by an ocean-facing window. Fully staffed with daily breakfast and a covered carport, set just a short drive from Fisherman's Village.",
